<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="expression-n">expression <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /ɪk'spreʃn/    美 /ɪk'spreʃn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c-u">1.★ <strong>[C] &amp; [U] 表达；表示：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>freedom of expression</strong>
言论自由</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I sent them flowers as an <strong>expression of thanks</strong>.
我给他们送去鲜花表示感谢。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It's better to <strong>give expression to</strong> your anger, rather than hiding it.
最好把你的愤怒表达出来，不要隐藏。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-look">2.★ <strong>表情；神色 (look)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The expression on her face is very friendly.
她脸上的表情很友好。</p><footer>外研② – 4</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I could tell from his expression that he was unhappy.
我从他的表情看出他不高兴了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>词语；措辞；表达方法：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You can learn interesting words and expressions by reading poems.
通过阅读诗歌，你能学到有趣的词语和表达方法。</p><footer>人教⑥ – 2</footer></div>

<h4 id="4u">4.<strong>[U] 感情；表现力：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>read / play with expression
有感情地朗读/表演</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (express) on his face told me that he was angry.  （2006 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. expression  </p></div>